    "Cliff's delta is used as the metric, where a negative value indicates the prompting technique became more effective over time at eliciting harmful content, while a positive value indicates it became less effective.",
    "Cells with p-values <0.05 are bolded, indicating statistical significance.The table offer insights into the evolution of baseline performance and the impact of jailbreaking on the effectiveness of GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 models.",
    "Firstly, regarding the baseline evolution without jailbreaking, it is observed that both GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 have undergone improvements in protecting against harmful content generation.",
